// https_test.ino — TLS cert-validation bench harness (#189 Phase B).
//
// Flash this on a device on the bench to PROVE the firmware's TLS validation is
// genuinely on before trusting it on a customer's network. It is self-contained
// (embeds the same Amazon root bundle as the product certs.h, plus a deliberately
// wrong CA), so the bench only needs WiFi creds below.
//
// What it proves, in one flash:
//   • SNTP syncs the clock first (TLS checks cert dates; ESP32 boots at 1970).
//   • POSITIVE: with the Amazon root bundle pinned, api.pihatankwatch.nz is
//     reachable over a VALIDATED connection (HTTP 401 = TLS ok, API reached).
//   • NEGATIVE: with a WRONG CA pinned (ISRG Root X1, which does not sign an
//     Amazon-fronted host), the handshake is REFUSED (code <= 0). This is the
//     test that distinguishes "validation is on" from "happy path happens to work".
//
// Before flashing: set WIFI_SSID / WIFI_PASS. Also run, on your workstation:
//   openssl s_client -showcerts -connect api.pihatankwatch.nz:443
// and confirm the chain's ROOT is one of Amazon Root CA 1-4 (matches certs.h).

